In this article, President Joe Biden expresses his appreciation for teachers and recognizes their dedication and selflessness in shaping the lives of students. He emphasizes the importance of in-person learning and the efforts made to safely reopen schools during the pandemic. President Biden highlights the American Rescue Plan's investment in schools to address the challenges caused by the pandemic, such as mental health support and lost learning. He acknowledges the underpayment of teachers and the need to increase compensation to attract and retain talented educators. The Department of Education is providing resources to help teachers meet student needs and is committed to diversifying the teaching profession. President Biden encourages Americans to support teachers through various activities and programs during National Teacher Appreciation Week.